<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0e673940-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s9583"><num value="9583">§ 9583.</num><heading> Removal</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0e673941-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s9583/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Presidential</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Director, each member of the Board, and the Commissioner for Education Statistics may be removed by the President prior to the expiration of the term of each such appointee.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0e673942-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s9583/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Director</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each Commissioner appointed by the Director pursuant to <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s9517">section 9517 of this title</ref> may be removed by the Director prior to the expiration of the term of each such Commissioner.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id0e673943-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/279/tI/s193">Pub. L. 107–279, title I, § 193</ref>, <date date="2002-11-05">Nov. 5, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1974">116 Stat. 1974</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
